data.content:
Created both files. Here's what the component does:

- **Generic** — `@typeparam TItem` lets it work with any type.
- **Internal copy** — `OnParametersSet` copies `Items` into a private `_items` list, so the parent's collection is never mutated.
- **Move Up / Move Down** buttons swap adjacent items, with buttons disabled at the boundaries.
- **`OnOrderChanged`** fires after each swap, passing an `IReadOnlyList<TItem>` snapshot so the parent can update its own state.

**Usage** (matches your example):

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { ... };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
